# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Planned 
- Local FIFO message memory cache for fast retrieval (update on events, fallback to Discord)
- Thread-aware context loading (default current thread, expand on request/need)
- Streaming responses for better UX
- Image and text attachment processing
- Advanced logging with full context
- Configuration validation for new features
- Error handling for attachments and memory
- Performance tests for cache and retrieval

## [0.3.0] - 2025-09-11

### Delivered
- Story DS-2.2A: Stack Operations complete, including DS-2.2A.1 Core Bot Interactions and DS-2.2A.2 Enhanced Features
- Core Discord bot functionality with slash commands, permissions, basic hot-reload, and memory enhancements
- Secure configuration with Docker secrets consolidation
- Comprehensive testing strategy and DoD for MVP delivery

### Added
- Thread-aware context loading and local FIFO memory cache (DS-2.2A.2)
- Enhanced acceptance criteria for advanced features

### Fixed
- Config.yaml secrets removed (placeholders only, loaded from Docker secrets)
- Changelog consolidation and version management

## [0.2.0] - 2025-09-10

### Added
- Docker secrets for credential management
- Credential masking in logs
- Read-only volume mounts and container security options
- Discord bot service integration with health checks and YAML configuration
- Docker Compose setup for bot stack with resource limits
- Structured logging with JSON/text formats and rotation
- Configuration validation with runtime and standalone tools
- Graceful shutdown with signal handling and task cancellation
- Comprehensive README and security documentation

### Changed
- Version bump from 0.1.1 to 0.2.0
- Migrated credentials to Docker secrets
- Enhanced health check logic for secrets validation

### Security
- All sensitive data stored in Docker secrets
- Automatic log masking for credentials
- Container hardening with read-only filesystem and no-new-privileges

## [0.1.1] - 2025-09-10

### Added

- MIT License file
- VERSION file for semantic versioning
- GitHub badges for project status and technology stack

## [0.1.0] - 2025-09-10

### Added

- Project directory structure with services/, stacks/, scripts/, and docs/ directories
- Makefile commands for stack management (bootstrap, up, down, logs, clean, rebuild, shell)
- Docker network management for multi-service communication
- Bootstrap script with dependency validation and environment initialization
- Service version tracking via services.lock.json lock file
- Project documentation and comprehensive .gitignore configuration